    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098894>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Konarus spp., A. K. cheiris female; B, K. cheiris male; C, K. cheiris male cheliped; D, K. crassicornis female; E, K. straddi male; F, K. straddi male cheliped. (A–C after Bamber, 2006; D after Bamber & Chatterjee, 2010; E–F after Bamber, 2008)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098894/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098898>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Konarus straddi comb. nov., A, female, dorsal, with A′, detail of carapace margin; B, antennule; C, antenna; D, labrum; E, left mandible; F, right mandible; G, labium; H, maxillule; I, maxilliped; J, epignath. Scale line = 1.0 mm for A, 0.2 mm for B to J." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098898/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098900>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Konarus straddi comb. nov., female, A, right cheliped; B, left cheliped (arrow indicates outer propodal apophysis bearing strong seta). Scale line = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098900/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10098902>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Konarus straddi comb. nov., female, A, pereopod 1; B, pereopod 2; C, pereopod 4; D, pereopod 6; E, pleopod (plumose nature of all setae not shown, most marginal setae shown only by their bases); F, pleotelson and right uropod. Scale line = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10098902/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

